content.detailedDescription: We were up at clatterin kist about to do a ceremony to celebrate the full moon.On the way to the kist we noticed bright white orbs through the trees no, notwhere the moon was. we first noticed the object after lighting a bright orangecandle and seeing a light blinking exactly the same colour over on the suiehill. we at first thought it was a mast, or car lights, but it soon becameevident that the movements and flashing pattern were too erratic for either ofthese, also too big to have been car lights at that distant. we both feltintense fear, and a sense of being watched and not welcomed. it was a veryuncomfortable feeling. the lights moved all over the hill, in front of both theforest and above the tree line, occasionally appearing in the sky above thehill. to the naked eye they appeared to flash on and off, then again in anotherposition, but through binoculars were observed to move while flashing. theyappeared in random sequence, and would remain lit for several seconds beforeflashing off. the colours changed between red and yellow although size remaineduniform and the number of objects increased from 1 to 4. the feeling of beingwatched and the sense of hostility increased, and as the number increased therewas a sensation of being closed in on, so we left the area as quickly andquietly as we could. when we returned to the car, the headlights seemed verydull and the night extremely dark with the moon low above the horizon. when weleft the vicinity of the suie hill, the lights brightened immediately, the skybecame lighter and more like a summers night, and the moon rose almostinstantly. on calm reflection, we realised that there are no masts on that hill,and no habitation.

content.detailedDescription: I was driving my car east to west between lordsburg, nm and safford, az alongi-10. i had just crossed the state line when a very violent thunderstorm wasmoving from west to east in the i-10 corridor. lightning, high winds,thunderhead clouds. following a thunderhead south of i-10 over the chiracuahamountains was a perfectly symetrical round hole in the cummulus cloud layerbehind the storm. i could see at least two other apparently perfectly roundholes in the cloud layer to the northwest and north, north of i-10, at greaterdistances. the hole to the south was, for estimating purposes, 4 miles south ofthe highway it could have been more and at least two or three miles indiameter--extremely large. as i drove east and watched the hole, after i hadgone through the storm, instantaneously an apparently perfectly round sphereslower 66 per cent appeared in the hole extending at least 3,000 below the cloudlayer, perhaps 500 off of the ground. it was grey, somewhat luminescent, withmist shrouding it. i watched it for about thirty seconds. a green fireball shotout of the sphere traveling in a direct line from the sphere east to west andaccelerated out of view within two or three seconds on a slightly inclinedplane, upward. as i was watching the sphere it vanished instantaneously i wouldsay became invisible again because i saw no motion with the sphere as itappeared or disappeared. it was hovering, no sounds that i could hear, no highspeed vibration. the hole in the cloud continued moving slowly in a west southwest direction, south of i-10 for at least 20 minutes at which time the holeslowly refilled with clouds until it was one continuous cloud layer.My first impression of the object was that it was huge and wasnt a flying disc.There were no secondary effects of the sighting to me or to the vehicle i wasdriving.Im interested if anyone else reports it. it happened yesterday afternoon.
content.summary: South east arizona very large sphere

content.summary: 3 lights in triangle formation over mountains
